                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origDate notAfter="1450" notBefore="1401">15th century, first half</origDate>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Origin and early provenance unknown. At some point the codex, which the fragments belonged to, ended up in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100242">Malmö</placeName>, where it was dismembered and the fragments used as covers/wrappings for financial accounts. This happened sometime before <date when="1553"/>, the year noted on <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>. The accounts belonged to the church and the hospital in Malmö. Later they were kept at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100162">archive of Malmö town hall </orgName>(<quote>Malmö rådhusarkiv</quote>).</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Transferred from the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100162">archive of Malmö town hall</orgName> to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> in <date when="1884"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
